One month ago, New Haven Firefighter, Ricardo Torres Jr, lost his life in the line of duty in my Connecticut hometown.  Tragically, he left behind his childhood sweetheart and pregnant wife, @errrcalynne, to raise their unborn son, Crew, and 1-year-old toddler, Oliver, without her rock & love of her life. 

Moments like this make many of us feel so helpless and insignificant, left only to pass along our condolences in person or on social media. 

So when the wife of New Haven’s Assistant Fire Chief and longtime friend, @colleendelaney_ called me to say that Ricardo’s widow was a HUGE fan of the @realhousewivesfranchise & that she and her husband, @jmcca1, wanted to put together a special video tribute to lift his widow spirits, it was my honor to leap into action and help make it happen.

I cannot thank @mrsjillzarin & @teresagiudice enough for immediately mobilizing their powerful connections on behalf of this incredible family.  You are two of the most altruistic & compassionate human beings I’ve ever met & it’s an honor to call you both friends. 🥰 

I am officially newfound fans of EVERY SINGLE HOUSEWIFE who took the time to send their love & support to Erica, Oliver, Crew and the entire @newhavenfireservice. 

Thank you for making Erica’s TODAY better than her YESTERDAY.

We love you @lisavanderpump @dorindamedley @jackiegoldschneider @therealmargaretjosephs @countessluann!!! 🇺🇸🚒👩‍🚒❤️🙏🏽

node.text:
As most of you know by now, I grew up idolizing both my epidemiologist father and his global health colleagues for their pioneering and renowned dedication to eradicating viral & microbial diseases across the world. 

As a result, it is genuinely heartbreaking to witness the lackadaisical and partisan deterioration of this once highly respected field and it’s various global health institutions. 

Thus - while sadly not surprising - the reckless disregard for the fundamental duty to SIMPLY PROVIDE ACCURATE INFORMATION by John’s Hopkins University & the CDC above is, once again, not only an irresponsible travesty, but tantamount to criminal negligence.

This is the kind of crap I would expect to see in some 14-year-old’s “if/then” hypothesis in Biology 101 — NOT a leading medical institution whose data directly dictates the daily guidance issued by every federal agency and public health entity in the country. 

“A massive 300 percent hike in nationwide COVID-19 deaths recorded Friday by Johns Hopkins University was skewed by states dumping data – that in one case dated back as far as last spring, according to a report.”

So basically, Johns Hopkins erroneously reported that deaths from the new Delta Variant “alarmingly jumped” from 321 to 891 in less than 24 hours. 

The mainstream media was all too happy to enthusiastically reiterate this false narrative. 

The correct figure?  321 deaths to 329. 

Sadly, I am not surprised. 

But what in the ACTUAL F. 😤😡

P.S.  473 Americans die each day in car accidents.  1700 from heart disease and 1600 from cancer. #CarryOn
